From: Horst von Brand [mailto:vonbrand@inf.utfsm.cl]
Subject: Re: devfs again, (was RE: USB device allocation) 
>> This is not needed... Don't believe the hype. With, or
>> without devfsd, you can
>> 
>> chmod
>> chown
>> ln -s
>> ls -l
>> mkfifo /tmp/hda && (cat /dev/hda > /tmp/hda &) && strings /tmp/hda >
>> /dev/null && echo "DUH"
>Do the changes stick after a reboot? After a crash (or power outage)?
>Can I rename the files, and the changes stay?
Any changes you make to the way you talk to kernel drivers should
be handled totally in userland, ie, devfsd. And renaming is dumb.
Just use ln.
What reason do you have to rename device nodes, other than to try
and find fault? Can I rename /proc/devices?
-Shawn
